<title>IRAQ: Saddam allows Iranians to visit Iraq holy shrines.</title>
<headline>Saddam allows Iranians to visit Iraq holy shrines.</headline>
<dateline>BAGHDAD 1997-08-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>President Saddam Hussein has decided to allow Iranians to visit holy shrines in Iraq beginning on September 4, Baghdad radio said on Monday.</p>
<p>&quot;President Saddam Hussein has instructed the authorities concerned to allow Iranian citizens to visit holy shrines in Iraq as from September 4,&quot; the radio said, quoting an official spokesman.</p>
<p>Such visits by Iranians were suspended at the start of the 1980-1988 Iraq-Iran War.</p>
